description: Ecuador closes all schools, from March 12 to April 5 UPDATE: On August 21st, the National Emergency Operations Committee (COE) will approve the plan for progressive and voluntary return to classes, which would be implemented starting September 1st. Sending students to face-to-face classes is voluntary, each school day will be four hours long, students will only go to school one day per week, and only 12 will be allowed in each classroom.

description:
Ecuador imposes a curfew from 21.00 to 5.00 on people, public transportation and other non-essentials residents.
Taxis and comparable services are just allowed to drive on certain days depending on the last digit on their serial number plate.

Ecuador imposes a curfew from 21.00 to 5.00, starting March 17 on all residents, excluding staff of medical, animal caring, banking, governmental, communication institutions and public services. Taxis and similar services are just allowed to drive on specific days depending on the last digit of their serial number plate.

description: On March 14th, "Ecuador’s government announced the closure of its borders from Sunday to all foreign travelers due to the spread of the coronavirus... Vice President Otto Sonnenholzner, in a televised statement, said all aerial, land and maritime transport into the Andean country will be prohibited... Ecuadorean citizens and foreigners with Ecuadorean residency will have until the end of Monday, March 16th, to return."
target_geog_level: All countries

description: "Ecuador will require all visitors to show COVID-19 test results that clear them of having the novel coronavirus... The new travel requirement, which takes effect May 21, 'will be mandatory,' and the test 'must have been done a maximum of 72 hours before boarding' a flight to Ecuador, Romo said via Twitter."
target_geog_level: All countries

description: On August 13th, the National Government of Ecuador released a new app to monitor the health of its residents. Each phone-user is given an anonymous code, and the phone detects when it is close in proximity to another phone's user who could be potentially contaminated. If a positive COVID case is suspected, the app presents steps to take to further promote health and safety.

description: On July 28th, Ecuador opens mobile centers for COVID-19 testing. Medical brigades despatched by the Health Ministry are also patrolling neighborhoods with high rates of infection to carry out spot tests."

description: The Ecuadorian Ministry of Works sets the rules of working from home. Every ministry and employer in the private sector has to look for options that employees can work from home ("teletrabajo"). If so, the employer is obliged to provide documents which employees can show to the police in case of questioning. Lost hours are to be made up by the employees. e.g. extra shifts after the crisis.
